{"lemma":"سَبْعَة","slug":"سَبْعَة","root":"س.ب.ع","root_slug":"س-ب-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ب-ع","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سَبْعَة","root":"سبع","pos":"N","occurrence_count":4},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","num"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n18743","n18752","n18753","n18754"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%92%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"num","gloss":"masculine of سَبْعَة (sabʕa, “seven”)","tags":["form-of","masculine"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"one seventh"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a beast of prey; a voracious animal","examples":[{"text":"حُرِّمَتْ عَلَيْكُمُ الْمَيْتَةُ وَالدَّمُ وَلَحْمُ الْخِنزِيرِ وَمَا أُهِلَّ لِغَيْرِ اللَّهِ بِهِ وَالْمُنْخَنِقَةُ وَالْمَوْقُوذَةُ وَالْمُتَرَدِّيَةُ وَالنَّطِيحَةُ وَمَا أَكَلَ السَّبُعُ إِلَّا مَا ذَكَّيْتُمْ وَمَا ذُبِحَ عَلَى النُّصُبِ وَأَن تَسْتَقْسِمُوا بِالْأَزْلَامِ"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root س ب ع (s b ʕ); compare سَبْعَة (sabʕa, “seven”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n18743","headword_ar":"سبّعهُ","root":"sbE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tasobiyEN","text_ar":"تَسْبِيعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made it seven;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"called it seven;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AsbEhu","text_ar":"اسبعهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) See also 1. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made it to have seven angles,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corners; to be heptagonal."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(God)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gave him his reward,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"recompense, seven times,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seven fold."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) An Arab of the desert said to a man who had done a good act to him, (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sab~aEa A@ll~`hu laka","text_ar":"سَبَّعَ ا@للّٰهُ لَكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God give thee thy reward,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"recompense, seven times,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seven fold."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) The Arabs also said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sab~aEa A@ll~`hu laka A^ajorahaA","text_ar":"سَبَّعَ ا@للّٰهُ لَكَ اَجْرَهَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God multiply to thee the reward,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"recompense, for it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning, for this good act: (Aboo-Sa'eed:) [for]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tasobiyEN","text_ar":"تَسْبِيعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used by them to signify the act of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"multiplying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"though it be more than seven fold. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sab~aEa A@ll~`hu lifulaAnK","text_ar":"سَبَّعَ ا@للّٰهُ لِفُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God make a thing to be followed by another thing to such a one;"},{"kind":"text","text":"in relation to good and to evil; as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tab~aEa lahu","text_ar":"تَبَّعَ لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sab~aEa A@ll~`hu laka","text_ar":"سَبَّعَ ا@للّٰهُ لَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God bless thee with seven children."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He washed it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(namely, a vessel,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seven times."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) Hence the saying of Aboo-Dhu-eyb,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"kanaEoti A@l~atiY qaAmato tusab~iEu suw^orahaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Like her who has arisen to wash out seven times her remains of beverage in the bottom of a vessel, left by a drinker;"},{"kind":"text","text":"that drinker, as is said in a marginal note in my copy of the TA, being her dog]: or, accord. to Es-Sukkaree, the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to give as alms her"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suw^or","text_ar":"سُوْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remains of beverage in the bottom of a vessel after one had drunk,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remains of food &c.,"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thereby seeking to have her reward,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"recompense, multiplied;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suw^orahaA","text_ar":"سُوْرَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"being used by the poet for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bisuw^orihaA","text_ar":"بِسُوْرِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sb~E AlquroA=na","text_ar":"سبّع القُرْا=نَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. followed by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu","text_ar":"لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He appointed him the reading,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"recitation, of the Kur-án"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in seven portions so that he should complete the whole"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in every seven nights."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, L, K.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sb~E liA@moraA^atihi","text_ar":"سبّع لِا@مْرَاَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EinodahaA","text_ar":"عِنْدَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahaA","text_ar":"لَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asobaEa","text_ar":"اَسْبَعَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He remained with his wife seven nights."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) In like manner one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"val~ava","text_ar":"ثَلَّثَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and thus of every number from one to ten; in relation to any saying or action. (TA.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sb~Et","text_ar":"سبّعت"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a woman)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brought forth at seven months."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sb~E daraAhimahu","text_ar":"سبّع دَرَاهِمَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made his dirhems to be seventy complete;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but this is post-classical; (K;) and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"drAhmh","text_ar":"دراهمه"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboEana","text_ar":"سَبْعَنَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning the same, and also post-classical, and not allowable; the proper phrase to express the meaning “ I made it to be seventy ” being"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kam~alotuhu saboEiyna","text_ar":"كَمَّلْتُهُ سَبْعِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sab~aEati Alqawomu","text_ar":"سَبَّعَتِ القَوْمُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"company of men, completed the number of seven hundred men:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) occurring in a trad, (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["God","TA","K"]},{"entry_id":"n18752","headword_ar":"سَبْعَةٌ","root":"sbE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) sometimes pronounced ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabaEapN","text_ar":"سَبَعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"but some disallow this latter, and say that it is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAbiEN","text_ar":"سَابِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Seven;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a well-known number; and called one of the perfect numbers:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboEN","text_ar":"سَبْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboEapu rijaAlK","text_ar":"سَبْعَةُ رِجَالٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Seven men"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboEu nisowapK","text_ar":"سَبْعُ نِسْوَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seven women"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*ahu A^axo*a saboEapK","text_ar":"اَخَذَهُ اَخْذَ سَبْعَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabuEapN","text_ar":"سَبُعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wazona saboEapK","text_ar":"وَزْنَ سَبْعَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Of the weight of seven"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mavaAqiyl","text_ar":"مَثَاقِيل"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*otu minohu miAy^apa dirohamK wazona saboEapK","text_ar":"اَخَذْتُ مِنْهُ مِايَةَ دِرْهَمٍ وَزْنَ سَبْعَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I took,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"received, from him a hundred dirhems"},{"kind":"text","text":"] every ten whereof were"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the weight of seven"},{"kind":"text","text":"mithkáls. (TA.) [But see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dirohamN","text_ar":"دِرْهَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iHodaY mino","text_ar":"اـِحْدَى مِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sboEK","text_ar":"سبْعٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One of seven;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a great, momentous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"difficult, thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh, K: *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an affair difficult to decide:"},{"kind":"text","text":"perhaps as being likened to one of the seven nights in which God sent the punishment upon [the tribe of] 'Ád: or, as some say, the seven years [of famine in the days] of Joseph. (Sh, TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~aboEu","text_ar":"السَّبْعُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmavaAniY","text_ar":"المَثَانِى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Fátihah;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"first chapter of the Kur-án;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] because it consists of seven verses: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the long chapters from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albaqarap","text_ar":"البَقَرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aEorAf","text_ar":"الاَعْراف"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^anofaAl","text_ar":"الاَنْفَال"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as in the Mufradát: or, as in the L,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~awobap","text_ar":"التَّوْبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", reckoning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Altwbp","text_ar":"التوبة"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlAnfAl","text_ar":"الانفال"},{"kind":"text","text":"as one chapter, for which reason they are not separated by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basomalap","text_ar":"بَسْمَلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mavonFY","text_ar":"مَثْنًى"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b6-  El-Farezdak says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"wakayofa A^axaAfu Aln~aAsa waA@ll~`hu qaAbiDN\n                      \n                     \n                        EalaY Aln~aAsi waAls~aboEayoni fiY raAHapi Alyadi"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And how should I fear men when God is comprehending mankind and"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the seven heavens and seven earths"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the palm of the hand?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) ―         -b7-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^usobuwEN","text_ar":"اُسْبُوعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; last sentence. ―         -b8-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboEapN","text_ar":"سَبْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also used in a vague manner, as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Seven"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"more;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"several;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"many;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as Bd says, in ix. 81, and as is indicated, though not plainly declared, in the TA. See 2: and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboEuwna","text_ar":"سَبْعُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b9-  Respecting a peculiar pronunciation of the people of El-Hijáz, and a case in which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboEap","text_ar":"سَبْعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is imperfectly decl., see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"valaAvapN","text_ar":"ثَلَاثَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sit~apN","text_ar":"سِتَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboEapa","text_ar":"سَبْعَةَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$ara","text_ar":"عَشَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[indecl. in every case, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Seventeen,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is pronounced by some of the Arabs"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboEapa Eo$ara","text_ar":"سَبْعَةَ عْشَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and [the fem.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboEa Ea$orapa","text_ar":"سَبْعَ عَشْرَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", thus in the dial. of El- Hijáz [and of most of the Arabs], is pronounced"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboEa Ea$irapa","text_ar":"سَبْعَ عَشِرَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the dial. of Nejd. (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E$r","text_ar":"عشر"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabuEapN","text_ar":"سَبُعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n18753","headword_ar":"سَبَعَةٌ","root":"sbE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboEapN","text_ar":"سَبْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n18754","headword_ar":"سَبُعَةٌ","root":"sbE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboEapN","text_ar":"سَبْعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", the latter a contraction of the former, The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lioness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, S, Msb, K.) Hence the saying, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*ahu A^axa*a saboEapK","text_ar":"اَخَذَهُ اَخَذَ سَبْعَةٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (ISk, S, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~aboEapi","text_ar":"السَّبْعَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He seized him with the seizing of a lioness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, S, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the lioness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) which is more impetuous ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anozaqu","text_ar":"اَنْزَقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":") than the lion, (ISk, S,) or more bold than the lion: (Msb:) or the saying is,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*ahu A^axo*a saboEapa","text_ar":"اَخَذَهُ اَخْذَ سَبْعَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he seized him with the seizing of Seb'ah,"},{"kind":"text","text":"who was a certain strong man, (Ibn-El-Kelbee, S,) or a certain insolent and audacious rebel, (Ibn-El-Kelbee, Lth, K,) of the Arabs, (TA,) whom one of the kings of El-Yemen seized, and, after having cut off his hands and feet, or arms and legs, crucified; [so that the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he punished him with the punishment of Seb'ah;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and hence it was said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA^uEa*~iban~aka Ea*aAba saboEapa","text_ar":"لَاُعَذِّبَنَّكَ عَذَابَ سَبْعَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will assuredly punish thee with the punishment of Seb'ah"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (El-Kelbee, Lth, K; *) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA^aEomalan~a bika Eamala saboEapa","text_ar":"لَاَعْمَلَنَّ بِكَ عَمَلَ سَبْعَةَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will assuredly do with thee as was done with Seb'ah:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O:) or the man's name was"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabuEN","text_ar":"سَبُعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and it was contracted, and made fem. by way of contempt: or the meaning of the first saying is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he seized him with the seizing of seven"},{"kind":"text","text":"men: (K:) and in like manner the last saying is expl. by some [who say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboEapK","text_ar":"سَبْعَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboEapa","text_ar":"سَبْعَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) The dim. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"subayoEapN","text_ar":"سُبَيْعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabuEN","text_ar":"سَبُعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["ISk","S","K","Msb","TA","O"]}]}}